news.title: Chinese developer Grandjoy gets $1.6 billion facility to fund M&A
news.para: Grandjoy said on its official account on WeChat late on Monday the facility would support its acquisitions and come in the form of loans, funds, securitisation and other financing products.

news.title: NBCC's net profit down 10% to Rs 87 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income also fell to Rs 2,056.31 crore in the third quarter of the fiscal from Rs 2,149.17 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Gurugram: Power supply to 16 societies soon as regulator gives nod
news.para: Power discom DHBVN had stopped providing new connections in these 16 colonies since July last year after the developers did not build the requisite power infrastructure.

news.title: Ansal Properties to invest Rs 46 crore for faster completion of projects
news.para: Out of the total Investment of approximately Rs 46 crore, approximately Rs 14.79 crore will be invested by ICP Investments (Mauritius) Limited, a Foreign Venture Capital Investors, against allotment of 87,00,000 warrants and balance will be invested by Promoter Group Entity.

news.title: FIR registered against six for conspiring to dupe plot buyers
news.para: According to senior administrative officials, six persons including Deepak Agrawal, his wife Swati Agrawal, Ghanshyam Agrawal, Ankul Agrawal (Angle Infratech), Chirag Shah and Gajraj Singh on the basis of fake power of attorney took illegal possession over at least 26 plots in Phoenix Township.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Income-tax department seizes Rs 13 crore cash and jewellery
news.para: According to the sources close to the development, the sleuths have found Rs 10 crore in cash along with ornaments worth Rs 3 crore.

news.title: Buildings survey underway along some Chennai metro phase-2 routes
news.para: As construction for phase-2 metro rail network is set to begin in several localities soon, teams of experts have started conducting a survey of buildings and structures located on some of the city’s busiest localities.

news.title: Shriram Properties posts Rs 13.2 crore profit in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income, however, fell to Rs 130.12 crore in the third quarter of the fiscal from Rs 161.70 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Property disputes dominate Hyderabad civic body cases pending in SC
news.para: Of 21 pending trials, the civic body is handling 14 of them pertaining to property disputes. These include encroachment on government land, land acquisition disputes, land grabbing, etc.

news.title: Rajasthan: Legal hurdle for bajri mining at 20 locations
news.para: ​​According to records, four mines each in Ajmer and Chittorgarh, three each in Bhilwara and Dausa, two each in Jaipur, Dholpur and Tonk and one each in Jhunjhinu, Jodhpur, Nagaur, Sirohi and Barmer will not be operational even with an environmental clearance (EC).

news.title: Chandigarh departments to list unsold properties
news.para: A senior UT official said there are a number of vacant properties of UT estate office, Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB), Municipal Corporation (MC), Industrial department and many other departments, which could not be sold as they were on leasehold.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Sealing looms if property tax dues exceed Rs 50,000
news.para: “From February 1 to 11 we have sealed 2,751 properties in the city whose pending tax amount exceeds Rs 1 lakh,” said Jainik Vakil, the chairman of the AMC’s revenue committee.

news.title: Centre won't allow Rajasthan to correct errors on housing portal
news.para: ​Out of the 2.01 lakh Pradhan Mantri Awaas Yojana-Grameen (PMAY-G) beneficiaries whose names were rejected by the Centre’s portal due to technical errors, 1.55 lakh were found eligible after physical verification, the state’s survey report said.

news.title: Kochi: Auditors find anomalies in revision of RAY project cost
news.para: According to the audit report for 2019-20, which is out now, around 975 dwelling units for poor could have been constructed using Rs 39 crore, which is the estimate prepared by local body for constructing just 199 units of 300 sq ft.

news.title: Greenply Industries' net profit up by 19% to Rs 29 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: The company's revenue during the October-December period of the 2021-22 fiscal was Rs 421.1 crore, up by over 23 per cent on a year-on-year (y-o-y) basis.
